In his account of the conferenee and compaot between Bruce and the Red Comyn at Perth, in the year 1304, Henry the Minstrel repeatedly applies the term augment to what Fordun describes as

“ conventio hincinde facta ao fide media, interpositis juramentis, per

“ suas indenturas, cum appositione sigillorum eorundem roborata.’'

The Bruoe and he completyt furth thar bandia3 Syn that samyn nycht thai sellyt with thar hamdis. This ragmant left the Bruce with Cumyn thar, With king Edward haym in England can far: And thar remaynyt quhill this augment war knnwin, Thre yer and mar or Bruce persewyt hia auin. ¹ Sum men demys that Cumyn that ragntent send; Sum men tharfor agaynys makia defend. nallatenus v. 1147.
